.TH "__class_create" 9 "__class_create" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
__class_create \- create a struct class structure
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct class *" __class_create
.BI "(struct module *owner "  ","
.BI "const char *name "  ","
.BI "struct lock_class_key *key "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "owner" 12
pointer to the module that is to "own" this struct class
.IP "name" 12
pointer to a string for the name of this class.
.IP "key" 12
the lock_class_key for this class; used by mutex lock debugging
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This is used to create a struct class pointer that can then be used
in calls to \fBdevice_create\fP.

Returns \fIstruct class\fP pointer on success, or \fBERR_PTR\fP on error.

Note, the pointer created here is to be destroyed when finished by
making a call to \fBclass_destroy\fP.
